---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for FRM Consulting Group (Aust) Pty Ltd. Learn how we collect, use, hold, disclose and protect your personal information.">

  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-navy py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="w-16 h-1 bg-frm-green mb-6"></div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          How we collect, use, hold, disclose and protect your personal information.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Effective date: 27 June 2026</p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        FRM Consulting Group (Aust) Pty Ltd (ACN 630 110 682) ("we", "us", "our", the "FRM Group") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, hold, disclose and protect your personal information, and applies to all of our websites, landing pages, forms and marketing.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We have adopted the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) contained in the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) (the Privacy Act). The APPs govern the way in which we collect, use, disclose, store, secure and dispose of your personal information. A copy of the APPs is available from the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-frm-green hover:underline">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.
      </p>

      <!-- What is personal information -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">What is personal information and why do we collect it?</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Personal information is information or an opinion that identifies, or could reasonably identify, an individual. The personal information we collect is primarily your contact and identifying details — for example your name, postal and email addresses, and phone numbers — together with information about how you interact with our websites, ads and communications.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We collect this information in a number of ways, including:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>when you register for a webinar, event or download;</li>
        <li>when you complete a form or enquiry on our websites or landing pages;</li>
        <li>by telephone, email or correspondence;</li>
        <li>when you interact with our advertising or pages on social media platforms (such as LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram and Google);</li>
        <li>through cookies and similar tracking technologies; and</li>
        <li>from publicly available sources and third parties (such as advertising and lead-generation platforms).</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We collect your personal information for the primary purposes of providing our services to you, responding to your enquiries, and marketing (including inviting you to events and webinars and following up with you). We may also use it for secondary purposes that are related to a primary purpose and that you would reasonably expect. Where appropriate, we will explain why we are collecting your information and how we intend to use it. You can opt out of our marketing at any time (see "Direct marketing" below).
      </p>

      <!-- Sensitive information -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Sensitive information</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We do not ordinarily collect "sensitive information" (as defined in the Privacy Act). If we ever need to collect sensitive information, we will only do so with your consent, or where required or authorised by law.
      </p>

      <!-- Direct marketing -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Direct marketing and how we contact you</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        By providing your details to us you agree that we and our group companies may contact you. Our marketing may include:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Phone calls</li>
        <li>Email and SMS/MMS</li>
        <li>LinkedIn messages and advertising</li>
        <li>Meta and Google advertising and retargeting</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You can opt out at any time — by using the unsubscribe link in our emails, replying STOP to an SMS, telling us during a call, or contacting us using the details at the end of this policy.
      </p>

      <!-- Cookies -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Cookies, tracking and online advertising</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Our websites use cookies and similar technologies (including the Meta Pixel, LinkedIn Insight Tag and Google Analytics/Google Ads tags) to understand how visitors use our sites, measure advertising, and show relevant ads. You can manage cookies through your browser settings.
      </p>

      <!-- Disclosure -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Disclosure of your personal information</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may disclose your personal information:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-navy">Within the FRM Group</strong> — to our subsidiary companies, including Surfside Accounting Services Pty Ltd, CDM Recruitment Partners Pty Ltd, Specialised Finance Australia Pty Ltd, Chamberlin Partners Pty Ltd, Property Management Australia (Qld) Pty Ltd, Task Force Consulting (Qld) Pty Ltd, Chamberlin, Collins &amp; Partners Pty Ltd, Solar Finance Australia Pty Ltd and Reno Finance Australia Pty Ltd, for the purposes described in this policy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-navy">To trusted partners and service providers</strong> — who assist us in operating our business and delivering services, subject to appropriate confidentiality and privacy obligations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-navy">With your consent</strong> — where you have given us permission to share your information.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-navy">In connection with business transfers</strong> — in the event of a merger, acquisition or sale of assets.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-navy">Where required by law</strong> — to comply with legal obligations, court orders or regulatory requirements.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Overseas disclosure -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Overseas disclosure</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Some service providers may store or process personal information outside Australia, including in the United States.
      </p>

      <!-- Security -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Security</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Your personal information is stored in a manner that reasonably protects it from misuse, interference and loss. Information is retained for a minimum of 7 years or as required by law.
      </p>

      <!-- Access and correction -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Access and correction</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You may request access to or correction of your personal information by contacting us using the details below.
      </p>

      <!-- Complaints -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Complaints</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you have a complaint about how we have handled your personal information, please contact us using the details below. We will investigate and respond to your complaint in a reasonable time. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-frm-green hover:underline">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.
      </p>

      <!-- Updates -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Updates</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.
      </p>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Contact</h2>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-100">
        <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-1">FRM Consulting Group (Aust) Pty Ltd</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">ACN 630 110 682</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Privacy Officer</p>

        <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="font-medium text-navy w-14 shrink-0">Post:</span>
            <span>Suite 22 Level 1, 21 South Coolum Rd, Coolum Beach QLD 4573</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="font-medium text-navy w-14 shrink-0">Email:</span>
            <a href="mailto:admin@frmcg.com.au" class="text-frm-green hover:underline">admin@frmcg.com.au</a>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="font-medium text-navy w-14 shrink-0">Phone:</span>
            <a href="tel:0417548823" class="text-frm-green hover:underline">0417 548 823</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
